General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 reintegration, time to re-placement, family reunification outcomes, cost
2 comparison compared to in-State care, and reintegration success.
3 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
4 Health and Human Services the nonrecurring sum of one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000)
5 for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to conduct the Temporary Placement Pilot Program, as enacted in
6 Section 1 of this act.
7 SECTION 4. Section 3 of this act becomes effective July 1, 2026. The remainder of
8 this act is effective when it becomes law.
